- Dynamics and transients: The mastering is dynamics‑preserving and keeps transient attack, and the drums are described as punchy and controlled. Those are direct matches to my dislike of overcompressed, glossy masters and my preference for punch and transient detail.
- Overall synergy: Taken together—close vocals, layered yet well‑separated instruments, restrained ambience, punchy drums and preserving mastering—the double‑LP embodies the “visceral, upfront” and dynamics‑honoring sound I favor.
Why I reject The Very Best of Linda Ronstadt
