Conclusion: The Expansive double‑LP aligns across multiple specific criteria I stated—front‑and‑center tactile midrange vocals, layered guitars/keys with tight separation, restrained reverb, punchy drums, and dynamics‑preserving mastering—while the Linda Ronstadt compilation, despite some positives, conflicts with my dislike of breathy, sparse, and subdued presentations. Therefore I select the Expansive double‑LP.

